          "text": [
            "<p><strong>Logic and Programming</strong></p><p>Computational Thinking is the ability to break a problem apart and apply math and logic to it so it can be solved efficiently and repeatedly. There are several tools to do this in CLUE, including a programming tile. Programs can read sensor data (including simulated sensors) or generate series of numeric inputs, then transform the numbers and use them to control outputs. You don&#x27;t need to know much to get started, except perhaps that 0 = off and 1 = on. Copy this question into your document to get started. </p>"
          ]
